repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:37:## UiScaleManager
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:39:`UiScaleManager` is a process-wide singleton that holds the current system scale value.
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:45:float scale = UiScaleManager::Get().GetScale();  // default: 1.0
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:48:UiScaleManager::Get().SetScale(1.5f);
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:51:Calling `SetScale()` does three things atomically:
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:53:2. Resets the effective scale cache of every registered layout root and its entire subtree.
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:56:> **Note:** `SetScale()` silently ignores `NaN`, zero, and negative values. Passing such a value is a no-op and logs an error.
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:62:Each `View` can override how it participates in the scale propagation via `SetUiScalePolicy()`.
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:67:view.SetUiScalePolicy(UiScalePolicy::INHERIT);   // default
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:68:view.SetUiScalePolicy(UiScalePolicy::ENABLED);
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:69:view.SetUiScalePolicy(UiScalePolicy::DISABLED);
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:74:| `INHERIT` | From parent (or `UiScaleManager` at root) | Default. Inherits scale through the tree. Most views should use this. |
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:75:| `ENABLED` | Always equals `UiScaleManager::GetScale()` | Always tracks the system scale, regardless of what the parent's policy is. |
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:82:The view inherits the effective scale from its parent. Since all views default to `INHERIT`, the system scale set on `UiScaleManager` naturally flows down the entire tree without any extra configuration.
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:87:// label.SetUiScalePolicy(UiScalePolicy::INHERIT); // implicit
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:99:panel.SetUiScalePolicy(UiScalePolicy::DISABLED);
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:105:UiScaleManager scale = 2.0
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:117:Use `ENABLED` when a specific view inside a `DISABLED` subtree must still track the system scale. `ENABLED` bypasses parent inheritance and always reads directly from `UiScaleManager`.
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:120:panel.SetUiScalePolicy(UiScalePolicy::DISABLED);
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:121:badge.SetUiScalePolicy(UiScalePolicy::ENABLED);  // scales even inside DISABLED panel
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:125:UiScaleManager scale = 2.0
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:141:- `UiScaleManager` scale = `2.0` (set at runtime)
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:158:If your custom view (implemented via `ViewImpl`) caches pixel-unit values, those caches must be invalidated when scale changes. Since `InvalidateMeasure()` is called automatically on the root when `SetScale()` fires, derived views that override `OnMeasure` / `OnArrange` receive fresh constraints and `effectiveScale` on each layout pass — no extra work is required.
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:168:| Apply system-wide scale change | `UiScaleManager::Get().SetScale(newScale)` |
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:169:| Read the current system scale | `UiScaleManager::Get().GetScale()` |
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:170:| Opt a subtree out of scaling | `view.SetUiScalePolicy(UiScalePolicy::DISABLED)` |
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:171:| Force a view to always track system scale | `view.SetUiScalePolicy(UiScalePolicy::ENABLED)` |
repos/dali-ui/wiki/Ui-Scale.md:172:| Reset to default inherited behavior | `view.SetUiScalePolicy(UiScalePolicy::INHERIT)` |
